track_notes: Queen Mountain is the second highest peak in Joshua Tree National Park. I call it an adventure hike because its strenuous, complex, and remote. There is no trail and you are very unlikely to see anyone. The hardest part is up the gully where you will have to follow your instincts: sometime you stay in the gully and sometimes you escape to the right to avoid steep, rock-choked sections. Also, there is a fun scramble up solid rock to reach the summit. And the summit is spectacular. If you dont mind difficult hiking, Queen Mountain is worth the effort.
track_title: Queen Mountain - An Excellent Adventure Hike

track_notes: This is about the only route Im aware of. ANother my cut more direct to the base of the mountain. Easy road to follow and then well worn, ducted route to the summit.
